1) Launch the instance as usual (allow all traffic by editing inbound rule)

2) sudo apt update

3) sudo apt install docker.io -y

4) sudo systemctl start docker

5) sudo systemctl enable docker

6) mkdir ~/docker-bind-demo

7) cd ~/docker-bind-demo

8) wget https://www.tooplate.com/zip-templates/2137_barista_cafe.zip 

9) sudo apt install unzip -y
   
10) ls

11) unzip folder_name

12) ls

13) cd folder name  (move to unzipped folder)

14) mv * ..  

15) sudo docker run -d --name nginx-live -p 8080:80 -v ~/docker-bind-demo:/usr/share/nginx/html nginx

16) Test in Browser  
http://<your-ec2-public-ip>:8080

17) nano ~/docker-bind-demo/index.html

ONCE YOU ENTER THE EDITOR, GO DOWN BY USING DOWNWORD KEY AND JUST EDIT SOMETHING LIKE CAFE KLANG TO CAFE XYZ
THEN,
CTRL+O (write changes),
ENTER (confirm),
CTRL+X (exit).

18) REFRESH
